<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9905574342187></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9905574342187><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=144&mid=9905574342187>sweet pathing error</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 22nd 2:50 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just completed this quest, level 19 druid newbie.  This is what I did (much info I learned were from other posts on this board):<br>1. Went to Queynos North, I gave Moodoro 2 gold (didn't hail, indifferent faction) he gave me the book container. He is at the far right past the entrance of queynos in and around a tavern, a purple guy.<br>2. Gave Moodoro 4 gold until he gave me the joker card which I gave back to him, got one page (took like 10 plat)<br>3. Went to Highpass hold, on like the second bridge if you are walking through the zone to the karana's, jump off into the pond, you'll see a hole underwater under the bridge.  Go in and walk around, under the little tent with barrels is where Dyllin loads.  Literally right under the little overhang.  I just went back here to camp every night and before I'd go to school I'd log on just to check.  Got home one day and he was just there.<br>4.  Killin' Dyllin:  There is a SWEET pathing error:  When he spawned I harmonied the wandering smugglers and the few visible ones.  Then I snared him from standing back against the wall opposite the overhang.  He walked to me, but his path makes him walk way over to a side tunnel and then back to you.  So this whole time I nuked.  Then as he rounded his corner and came back I walked to where he spawns and he had to go back down his path, not straight to me.  Seriously, you can just move back and forth from the overhang to the wall and make him go back and forth along this weird path in the room.  He walks close to the entrance to the tunnel with the Rogue trainer smugglers, but not close enough to piss them off.  <br>5.  Put the 2 pages into the book and combined, woo!<br>Good luck in finding him, I didn't bother with camping, just kept checking back over like a week at start and end of the day.  Try out the pathing error (unless you are too high level to care).  like 6 nukes or so killed him, and I took basically nothing<br>Michaell Bolton<br>hehe, on erollosi mar ( dunno silly spelling)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
