	   <tr><td colspan=2>I completed this quest last night (Sunday, 5/20/01).  I was on my way from Lavastorm to Qeynos to start this quest, and I was passing through High Pass, and I figured let me check out Dylinn.  I had a friend show me the way there, and I was given the camp from a high level Druid (Thanks Kinloo!!!).  After about 3 hours of waiting, Dylinn finally spawned... He conned Yellow to me (15th lvl Druid).  I was very excited.  Casted Snare, resisted, casted Root, resisted.  He started whacking me, and I him.  I died when the red guy came back (luckily I was bound in the entrance to High Hold).  Mem'ed SOW, and Ignite, and ran back.  Two other people that were waiting with me were now corpses.  They did try to help me out though, so thanks to them as well. <br><br>When I got back, that high lvl Druid was waiting, and Dylinn was standing right behind the big red guy...<br><br>This time, I decided to go with my original plan, and I harmonized the blue guy, while the other Druid harmonized the red guy.  When both stuck, I rooted (Worked this time), and started whacking/igniting away.  I was getting my butt kicked, but thankfully Kinloo came in with a quick heal, and a quick blast, and it was over.  VICTORY!!!<br><br>After that, ran to Qeynos, spent about 1 1/2 hours looking for the Crow's nest, and when I found it I KICKED MYSELF!!!  For any who don't know, it's pretty much right at the entrance from Qeynos Hills (just go in, and go to the right).<br><br>So, when I conned him, he was dubious.  I was kinda nervous about giving up my hard earned money, but I figured you only live once, right? (LOL!!!!)<br><br>Handed him the 2gp, and viola!  I got the book.  Started handing him 4gp at a time, and in 3 cards, drew the Jester, and BAM!  Now I have the Testament.<br><br>Thanks for the help all!!!<br><br>Aeolas<br>Druid of the 15th Season<br>Resides in Morell-Thule.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
