	   <tr><td colspan=2>After reading all of the posts here, I decided to give this quest a try.  I had been hunting down in Kunark, so I tp'd over to tox and took the boat from Erudin to Qeynos, which seemed faster than if I would have ran from the NK druid ring down to Qeynos.  Anyhow, I didn't bother talking to any of the Erudites OMW to Qeynos.  I was a bit worried about faction, so I chose to keep camo up all the way from the tox druid ring to the docks...and then from the Qeynos docks up to the NW corner of N Qeynos.  Targeted Moodoro while I was still invis and then went outside and north of the pond (sewer entrance) and dropped invis to see what he con'd to me.  Dubiously, so I put camo up again..went back to Moodoro and just tried giving him 2gp as several others here had suggested.  It worked; he gives the book container.  Giving him 4gp gets you a random card; I got lucky and got the jester on my 9th try.  Returned the jester card to Moodoro for pg 34.  Tp'd to NK and ran over to Highpass..located Starshine and dispatched him very easily at lvl 23.  He, of course, gave pg 30 and a rolled up note.  I don't know if this next part matters or not, but I placed pg 30 in the left slot of the testament book container and pg 34 in the right-hand side slot...clicked combine and WOOT =)  Got the Testament of Vanear.  I'm probly KOS in Qeynos now as the guards that I con'd were apprehensive (at least in north Qeynos), but I think it's worth it for this item.  Just wanted to confirm the fact that the Erudin part of this quest is just fluff and can be skipped entirely with no effect on the quest.  Also, whoever gave the advice to wait for the red con smuggler to head back to the water before ya try and kill Starshine is exactly right.  I didn't temp fate and let that smuggler be around to see his buddy go down, but I could see that if ya can't take Starshine down in 2 minutes or less...better get a group together or wait until ya can.  <br><br>23 wood-elf druid<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
