	   <tr><td colspan=2>After finding out about the Combine TP Room (TD, it's awesome) I took up exploring a little and ended up in Halas (no necros come this way, so there were a LOT of bonechips to buy -=P) anyway....messed around in BB...so I bound there and had to take the long way back....this quest was so much easier than I ever thought it would be.... <br>Hit Moodoro<br>Give him the 2gp for the book, and play the game..shouldn't take too long to get the Joker (and for the final prize, it's 1000% worth it!)<br>So ya got the book, and one page...<br><br>Head to HH, and to the Underwater passage to the Smuggler area (just below the bridge by Tiger's Den..<br><br>I think cuz ppl figure this is sort of a waste of time to wait 8 hours, not as many ppl are camping him (I always thought he would be camped 24 hours -=P so I never tried this before)..I got there and he wasn't under the tent..and I was ready to leave, and wamm...he pops...(about 3pm CST..so someone must have got him late last night, unless his spawn rate isn't that long).<br><br>I defeated him at level 16! (Druid)<br>What ya gotta do is hang around the tree across from him (I was hiding, didn't want to take chances)..as a Druid, I buffed up just as the patrolling Smuggler stopped along the wall for his rest (about 15-20 seconds, I think)...totally buffed (Skin like Rock, FireFist, Strength of Earth, and Thistlecoat)...<br>Dyllin didn't aggro against me (as I guess I don't mess with the smugglers...let's see how they like me walking thru with the book -=P), so I could stand next to ready to fight as soon as I was ready....<br><br>He Conned black(white) to me, so he's level 16..<br>Fights like a Rogue of that level too (from bandit experience) except with a little added punch, probably from the stress of getting killed twice a day -=P<br>Root is a must!! You have to either be able to make that final blast before he starts walking (yeah, he chickens out at the last moment...like most rogues...) For me, fighting and blasting (I had on a 7pt Damage shield even!) I couldn't kill him fast enough not to attract a rogue, luckily the Red didn't come, I think it was from the lookout point above....so, at that last moment, of "I'm not gunna make it!!" and "I'm doing it! I'm doing it!! So close!!"...I was being beaten on by a blue smuggler while dealing those final hits to Dyllin...it's true what they say about the feeling of Victory, it is SWEEET!!!! Whole body tingling with excitement, I killed him (at &lt;1 bubble of life and losing), fumbled for the loot (grabbed the letter first! ack!) ...got both, yelled (you will too! -=P), and I slowly walked off...delirious from excitement...actually tried pulling off a camou to run out of there (yeah, with a smuggler on my back)...well, didn't make it...but I had the loot so I waited to load..and BAMM!! I got my book!!  You can too! it's so easy!<br><br>WARNING: AFTER COMBINING PAGES, YOU WILL JUMP UP AND TELL EVERYONE IN THE HOUSE ABOUT IT, REGARDLESS OF THEM KNOWING WHAT THE HECK YER TALKING ABOUT.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
